# COPY . . copies everything from your project into the image. Without a filter, that includes stuff you absolutely don't want in there. A .dockerignore works exactly like .gitignore — it tells Docker "skip these when copying."

# Why it matters (not just tidiness):
# - .venv/ — your local virtual environment. It's built for your machine's paths; copying it in is useless and it's big (slow builds). The container builds its own deps via pip install.
# - .env — security. This has your Gmail app password. You do not want secrets baked into an image. On Render you'll set these as environment variables instead.
# - db.sqlite3 — your local dev database. Shouldn't travel into a production image.
# - .git/, __pycache__/ — pointless bloat.

.venv/
.env
db.sqlite3
.git/
.gitignore
__pycache__/
*.pyc
media/
test_media/
tests/
.claude/
